snippet.textDisplay: Messi is fed up of pathetic signings. He is not vs Valverde. Coach did everything he could with what he has and despite the psychological downfall vs Roma and Liverpool and the style, it was productive, disciplined and won games. Yes it was a Messi-carried team and I am not defending Valverde. He made mistakes. Everyone has his strenghts and weaknesses. Abidal and the board (however they vote and do it) brought half of the France national team. They may be the best international team right now, but you don't just bring everyone because they won the world cup when they are clearly misfits, injury prone or clearly not needed.  If I can somehow defend Lenglet and Umtiti signings, I can't justify Dembele and Griezmann. Pep and Laporte era was as much as tiki taka as about spanish speaking players, unity, personal mentality and understanding. I think that today they look divided not only on the pitch. I am sure that Xavi, who is a football genius and I heard that from Pep himself, that the guy is so devoted to this sport that he watches 3rd division games is the next successor to Cruyff and Pep, rejected the offer just because he sees what the board does. Unfortunately for Messi, the big rebuild when Xavi comes will be years from now with another board and he will be long gone.
